It is recommended to set\nthese parameters as they prove to be extremely useful to categorize your\nmetrics and search by them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eName\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eType\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eRequired\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSourceName\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eName of the metrics source. \u003ccode\u003e_sourceName\u003c/code\u003e can be used to search metrics from this source. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eString\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSourceHost\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eName of metrics host. \u003ccode\u003e_sourceHost\u003c/code\u003e can be used to search metrics from this host. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eString\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSourceCategory\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eCategory of the collected metrics. \u003ccode\u003e_sourceCategory\u003c/code\u003e can be used to search metrics from this category. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eString\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eDimensions\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eKey value pairs that contribute to identifying a metric. Collectd data have intrinsic dimensions with keys as \u003ccode\u003ehost\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eplugin\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eplugin_instance\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003etype_instance\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eds_name\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eds_type\u003c/code\u003e. The Additional dimensions specified here can help separating metrics collected from this collectd instance with metircs collected from other collectd instances. Dimensions cannot contain \u003ca href=\"#reserved-symbols\"\u003eReserved symbols\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"#reserved-keywords\"\u003eReserved keywords\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSrings in the format of \u003ccode\u003e\"key1\"=\"val1\", \"key2\"=\"val2\"\u003c/code\u003e ...\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMetadata\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eKey value pairs that do not contribute to identifying a metric. Metadata are primarily used to assist in searching metrics. Collectd data may have internal metadata. The additional metadata specified here can be used to enrich the existing metadata set. Metadata cannot contain \u003ca href=\"#reserved-symbols\"\u003eReserved symbols\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"#reserved-keywords\"\u003eReserved keywords\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSrings in the format of \u003ccode\u003e\"key1\"=\"val1\", \"key2\"=\"val2\"\u003c/code\u003e ...\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAddMetricDimension\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eIf set to \u003ccode\u003etrue\u003c/code\u003e adds new dimension named \u003ccode\u003emetric\u003c/code\u003e to every data point which consists of \u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003etype_instance\u003c/code\u003e concatenated using \u003ccode\u003eMetricDimensionSeparator\u003c/code\u003e. By default it is set to \u003ccode\u003eTrue\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBoolean\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMetricDimensionSeparator\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eString used to concatenate \u003ccode\u003etype\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003etype_instance\u003c/code\u003e while creating \u003ccode\u003emetric\u003c/code\u003e dimension. See \u003ccode\u003eAddMetricDimension\u003c/code\u003e option. By default it is \u003ccode\u003e.\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eString\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\n\u003c/table\u003e\n\u003cdiv dir=\"auto\"\u003eYou can configure the Sumo Logic collectd plugin by overriding default\nvalues for plugin parameters.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eName\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eDescription\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eType\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eDefault\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eUnit\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMaxBatchSize\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin batches metrics before sending them over https. MaxBatchSize defines the upper limit of metrics per batch.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e5000\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNA\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMaxBatchInterval\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin batches metrics before sending them through https. MaxBatchInterval defines the upper limit of duration to construct a batch.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSecond\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eHttpPostInterval\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin schedules https post requests at fixed intervals. HttpPostInterval defines the frequency for the scheduler to run. If no metrics batch is available at the time, the sceduler immediately returns. If multiple metrics batches are available, then the oldest batch is picked to be sent.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Float\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e0.1\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMaxRequestsToBuffer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin buffers failed and delayed metrics batch requests. MaxRequestsToBuffer specifies the maximum number of these requests to buffer. After the buffer becomes full, the request with oldest metrics batch will be dropped to make space for new metrics batch.\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e1000\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRetryInitialDelay\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. RetryInitialDelay specifies the initial delay before a retry is scheduled. More information can be found in the retry library\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNon-negative Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e0\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSecond\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRetryMaxAttempts\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. RetryMaxAttempts specifies the upper limit of retries before the current retry logic fails. The metric batch is then either put back for the next run (when metrics buffer specified by MaxRequestsToBuffer is not full), or dropped (when metrics buffer is full). More information can be found in the retry library\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNA\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRetryMaxDelay\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. RetryMaxDelay specifies the upper limit of delay before the current retry logic fails. Then the metric batch either is put back for the next run (when metrics buffer specified by MaxRequestsToBuffer is not full), or dropped (when metrics buffer is full). More information can be found in the retry library\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ePositive Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e100\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSecond\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRetryJitterMin\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. RetryJitterMin specifies the minimum extra seconds added to delay between attempts. More information can be found in the retry library\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNon-negative Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e0\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSecond\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRetryJitterMax\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. RetryJitterMax specifies the maximum extra seconds added to delay between attempts. More information can be found in the retry library\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNon-negative Integer\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSecond\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eEnableInternalMetrics\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eEnable the plugin's internal metrics. See \u003ca href=\"#plugin-internal-metrics\"\u003ePlugin Internal Metrics\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBoolean\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003efalse\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNA\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eSignalFxStatsDTags\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eEnable extracting metadata from metrics using SignalFx' extension to the StatsD protocol. See: \u003ca href=\"https://docs.signalfx.com/en/latest/integrations/agent/monitors/collectd-statsd.html#adding-dimensions-to-statsd-metrics\" This should be given when <a href="https://help.sumologic.com/Send-Data/Sources/02Sources-for-Hosted-Collectors/HTTP-Source/zGenerate-a-new-URL-for-an-HTTP-Source" rel="nofollow">creating the HTTP Source</a> on Sumo Logic web app.</td><td>String</td><td>True</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h4 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Basic parameters</h4><a id="user-content-basic-parameters" class="anchor-element" aria-label="Permalink: Basic parameters" href="#basic-parameters"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div><p dir="auto">The parameters below are not strictly required. It is recommended to setthese parameters as they prove to be extremely useful to categorize yourmetrics and search by them.</p><table><thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Description</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>SourceName</td><td>Name of the metrics source. <code>_sourceName</code> can be used to search metrics from this source. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.</td><td>String</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>SourceHost</td><td>Name of metrics host. <code>_sourceHost</code> can be used to search metrics from this host. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.</td><td>String</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>SourceCategory</td><td>Category of the collected metrics. <code>_sourceCategory</code> can be used to search metrics from this category. It will override the default configured in the the Sumo Logic Source configuration.</td><td>String</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>Dimensions</td><td>Key value pairs that contribute to identifying a metric. Collectd data have intrinsic dimensions with keys as <code>host</code>, <code>plugin</code>, <code>plugin_instance</code>, <code>type</code>, <code>type_instance</code>, <code>ds_name</code>, <code>ds_type</code>. The Additional dimensions specified here can help separating metrics collected from this collectd instance with metircs collected from other collectd instances. Dimensions cannot contain <a href="#reserved-symbols">Reserved symbols</a> and <a href="#reserved-keywords">Reserved keywords</a></td><td>Srings in the format of <code>"key1"="val1", "key2"="val2"</code> ...</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>Metadata</td><td>Key value pairs that do not contribute to identifying a metric. Metadata are primarily used to assist in searching metrics. Collectd data may have internal metadata. The additional metadata specified here can be used to enrich the existing metadata set. Metadata cannot contain <a href="#reserved-symbols">Reserved symbols</a> and <a href="#reserved-keywords">Reserved keywords</a></td><td>Srings in the format of <code>"key1"="val1", "key2"="val2"</code> ...</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>AddMetricDimension</td><td>If set to <code>true</code> adds new dimension named <code>metric</code> to every data point which consists of <code>type</code> and <code>type_instance</code> concatenated using <code>MetricDimensionSeparator</code>. By default it is set to <code>True</code>.</td><td>Boolean</td><td>False</td></tr><tr><td>MetricDimensionSeparator</td><td>String used to concatenate <code>type</code> and <code>type_instance</code> while creating <code>metric</code> dimension. See <code>AddMetricDimension</code> option. By default it is <code>.</code>.</td><td>String</td><td>False</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h4 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Additional overflow-auto" dir="auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="dimensions  metadata value timestamp"><pre><span class="pl-c1">dimensions  metadata value timestamp</span></pre></div><p dir="auto"><code>dimensions</code> and <code>metadata</code> are key/value pairs of strings separated by two spaces.<code>dimensions</code> uniquely identifying a metric, while <code>metadata</code> do not contribute to identifying a metric.Instead, they are used to categorize metrics for searching.<code>value</code> is a double number.<code>timestamp</code> is a 10-digit UNIX epoch timestamp.</p><p dir="auto">Example data before compression:</p><div class="highlight highlight-text-shell-session notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" dir="auto" MaxBatchSize defines the upper limit of metrics per batch.</td><td>Positive Integer</td><td>5000</td><td>NA</td></tr><tr><td>MaxBatchInterval</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin batches metrics before sending them through https. MaxBatchInterval defines the upper limit of duration to construct a batch.</td><td>Positive Integer</td><td>1</td><td>Second</td></tr><tr><td>HttpPostInterval</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin schedules https post requests at fixed intervals. HttpPostInterval defines the frequency for the scheduler to run. If no metrics batch is available at the time, the sceduler immediately returns. If multiple metrics batches are available, then the oldest batch is picked to be sent.</td><td>Positive Float</td><td>0.1</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>MaxRequestsToBuffer</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin buffers failed and delayed metrics batch requests. MaxRequestsToBuffer specifies the maximum number of these requests to buffer. RetryInitialDelay specifies the initial delay before a retry is scheduled. More information can be found in the retry library</td><td>Non-negative Integer</td><td>0</td><td>Second</td></tr><tr><td>RetryMaxAttempts</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. More information can be found in the retry library</td><td>Positive Integer</td><td>10</td><td>NA</td></tr><tr><td>RetryMaxDelay</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions. Then the metric batch either is put back for the next run (when metrics buffer specified by MaxRequestsToBuffer is not full), or dropped (when metrics buffer is full). More information can be found in the retry library</td><td>Positive Integer</td><td>100</td><td>Second</td></tr><tr><td>RetryJitterMin</td><td>Sumo Logic collectd plugin retries on recoverable exceptions.
